\" id=\"trap_topg_3\"><div class=\"webtop\"><span class=\"idm\" id=\"trap_idm_1\">to fall into/avoid the trap of doing something</span> </div></div></div><ol class=\"sense_single\" htag=\"ol\"><li class=\"sense\" hclass=\"sense\" id=\"trap_sng_17\" htag=\"li\"><a class=\"open oup_icons\" title=\"Add to My Word Lists\"><span class=\"star-btn\" aria-hidden=\"true\">​</span></a><span class=\"sensetop\" hclass=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\"><span class=\"def\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"def\">to do/avoid doing something that is a mistake but that seems at first to be a good idea</span></span><ul class=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\" hclass=\"examples\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">Parents often fall into the trap of trying to do everything for their children.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">The movie avoids the trap of spending too much time explaining things.</span></li></ul>      </li></ol></span></div><span class=\"dictlink-g\"><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/american_english/avoid\" title=\" definition in American English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">avoid</span></a> in the Oxford Advanced American Dictionary</span><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/academic/avoid\" title=\" definition in Academic English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">avoid</span></a> in the Oxford Learner's Dictionary of Academic English</span></span><div class=\"pron-link\">Check pronunciation:\n                        <a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/pronunciation/english/avoid\">avoid</a></div></div>\n","matches":[],"relatives":[],"nearBys":["avocation noun","avocet noun","avoid verb","avoidable adjective","avoidance noun"]},[]]